                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. LUCAS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">WILD</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-826" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-826" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-826" type="surname" value="MOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-826" type="given" value="MARIA EVELING"></interp>MARIA EVELING MOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Taylor—on the 10th Feb. the prisoner came to my master's shop—he gave me a bad shilling—I bit it, and gave it to my master—he cut it in two, then came to the prisoner and gave him one of the halves—the prisoner said he had no right to cut it—I went for an officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-827" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-827" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-827" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-827" type="given" value="WILLIAM HAYWARD"></interp>WILLIAM HAYWARD TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I have heard the evidence which Mott has given—it is correct—I gave the prisoner to the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-828" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-828" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-828" type="surname" value="CASTLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-828" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY CASTLE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 135.) On the 10th of Feb., I was called and took the prisoner—Mr. Taylor gave me this half of a shilling—I asked the prisoner if he had any more about him—he said no he had not,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184302270168"></xptr>
               <p>and I should not search him till I got to the station—I put my hand into his pocket, and found another bad shilling—he said a sailor gave them to him for carrying a parcel—he had no good money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-829" type="witnessName">
